# Accessibility with non-standard UI

- Every custom interaction (canvas, graph) must have an **accessible equivalent**: list mode / buttons / focus visible — see components in `src/app/components/`.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`: the `reduce-motion` class on `documentElement` is set in [`src/main.js`](src/main.js); disable or shorten decorative animations in CSS (`html.reduce-motion`).
- Announce content changes relevant to the user via **`aria-live`** where appropriate (e.g. detail panel).
- Keep the **skip link** in [`index.html`](index.html) and a sensible heading hierarchy.
